idea-plugin.description:
      This plugin adds support for opening tasks from annotations values. <br/>
      List of annotations should be customized at Project Settings -&gt; Tasks -&gt; Navigation. <br/>

      Sample: <br/>
      You have annotation <br/>
      <code><pre>
package util;
import java.lang.annotation.*;
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})
public @interface TestFor {
    String[] issues() default {};
}
      </pre></code> <br/>
      And you use it to annotate test classes or methods. <br/>
      <code><pre>
package tests;

public class TestClass {
    @util.TestFor(issues = {"IDEA-107660"})
    public String testSomething() {
        return myName;
    }
}
      </pre></code> <br/>
      Assume you have "util.TestFor#issues" defined in settings.<br/>
      And you also should have Tasks Server defined for issues resolving. (youtrack.jetbrains.com in my case)<br/>

      Now, "Go to Definition" on string literal "IDEA-107660" will open http://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-107660 in your browser.<br/>
      Also documentation for string literals provides some issue information.<br/>
